  "text": "To implement a minimal GCC GIMPLE optimization pass, I analyzed the following key GCC source files:\n\n1. **gcc/tree-pass.h** - Contains the definition of the pass infrastructure:\n   - Defines `pass_data` struct (lines 40-64) that contains metadata about a pass including type, name, properties required/provided, and todo flags\n   - Defines `opt_pass` base class (lines 73-113) with virtual methods `gate()` and `execute()`\n   - Defines `gimple_opt_pass` class (lines 116-123) which inherits from `opt_pass` for GIMPLE-level passes\n   - Contains declarations of factory functions like `make_pass_*()` for creating pass instances\n\n2. **gcc/tree-ssa-dce.cc** - A complete example of a working GIMPLE pass (Dead Code Elimination):\n   - Defines static `pass_data` structure (lines 2038-2049) with pass metadata:\n     - Type: GIMPLE_PASS\n     - Name: \"dce\"\n     - Properties required: PROP_cfg | PROP_ssa\n     - Timevar: TV_TREE_DCE\n   - Defines `pass_dce` class (lines 2082-2096) that inherits from `pass_dce_base`\n   - Implements `gate()` method (line 2055) that checks if pass should run\n   - Implements `execute()` method (lines 2091-2094) that performs the optimization\n   - Implements `clone()` method (line 2090) for pass instances\n   - Defines factory function `make_pass_dce()` (lines 2100-2104) that creates pass instances\n   - Uses `dump_file` and `dump_flags` for debug output (lines 189-194 in mark_stmt_necessary)\n\n3. **gcc/timevar.def** - Contains timevar ID definitions used in pass_data structs:\n   - Defines TV_TREE_SSA and other tree-pass related timevar IDs\n   - These are used in the tv_id field of pass_data structs\n\nThe implementation follows GCC's established patterns:\n- Pass classes inherit from `gimple_opt_pass` and override `gate()` and `execute()` methods\n- The `gate()` method returns true/false to control whether the pass runs\n- The `execute()` method returns an unsigned int containing TODO flags indicating what cleanup/verification is needed\n- Factory functions with signature `gimple_opt_pass *make_pass_name(gcc::context *ctxt)` create pass instances\n- Static `pass_data` structs define metadata including pass type, name, required/provided properties, and timevar ID\n- Debug output uses `dump_file` and `dump_flags` for conditional printing\n- The pass is placed in an anonymous namespace to avoid name collisions"
